Social humanities care 

課程概述 Course Description
       學生於本科目中藉由家庭訪視與社區/人群評估活動得以深入瞭解家庭與社區之健康問題，並於護理過程中嚐試整合、應用相關的學理知識以滿足家庭與社區之健康需求。認識社區中健康照護體系之運作，以瞭解其如何推動社區健康營造活動，進而瞭解現階段台灣社區護理狀況，並研討公共衛生護理未來展望。This course is designed to help students to explore the perspectives of community health nursing including roles and functions of community health nurses, the operation of health care delivery system and social resources related to community health. The course also helps students to identify factors which have impact on community health. Also, help them to recognize the contemporary community health problems in groups/ populations to maintain or promote their health status. The course also requires students to experience self health promotion activities.
Each student is required to have 120 clinical hours in one semester. To complete this course, students will be assigned to one of the primary health care center near Tainan city. During the clinical hours, students will visit at least 2 families for several times to experience family care. Community assessment is also a required learning experience in the course. This course aims at helping students to be able to assess families' health status and try to plan appropriate interventions.    

課程學習目標 Course Objectives
應用與社區護理相關之理論與知識於護理實習中應用護理過程評估社區之健康狀態，並計劃、執行與評價社區護理活動學得如何整合溝通理論與技巧與個人、家庭和同伴有效地溝通應用教與學的知識於家庭護理實務與教育中引導學生重視並呈現對護理實務之責任感協助學生面對所評估到的問題能應用實證研究成果在護理過程中之可行性應用領導與管理之概念，瞭解社區人群的管理及組織運作評價社區護理人員的角色如何滿足社會的健康需求 

